#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.34"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.34:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.34:0.2"
msgid "4. Cakkavagga"
msgstr "4. Situations"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.34:0.3"
msgid "34. Aggappasādasutta"
msgstr "34. The Best Kinds of Confidence"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.34:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, aggappasādā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four kinds of confidence are the best."

msgctxt "an4.34:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

#. VAR: dvipadā → dipadā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.34:1.3"
msgid ""
"Yāvatā, bhikkhave, sattā apadā vā dvipadā vā catuppadā vā bahuppadā vā "
"rūpino vā arūpino vā saññino vā asaññino vā nevasaññināsaññino vā, tathāgato "
"tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho."
msgstr ""
"The Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, is said to "
"be the best of all sentient beings—be they footless, with two feet, four "
"feet, or many feet; with form or formless; with perception or without "
"perception or with neither perception nor non-perception."

msgctxt "an4.34:1.4"
msgid "Ye, bhikkhave, buddhe pasannā, agge te pasannā."
msgstr "Those who have confidence in the Buddha have confidence in the best."

msgctxt "an4.34:1.5"
msgid "Agge kho pana pasannānaṃ aggo vipāko hoti."
msgstr "Having confidence in the best, the result is the best."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.34:2.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvatā, bhikkhave, dhammā saṅkhatā, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo tesaṃ "
"aggamakkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"The noble eightfold path is said to be the best of all conditioned things."

msgctxt "an4.34:2.2"
msgid "Ye, bhikkhave, ariye aṭṭhaṅgike magge pasannā, agge te pasannā."
msgstr ""
"Those who have confidence in the noble eightfold path have confidence in the "
"best."

msgctxt "an4.34:2.3"
msgid "Agge kho pana pasannānaṃ aggo vipāko hoti."
msgstr "Having confidence in the best, the result is the best."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.34:3.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvatā, bhikkhave, dhammā saṅkhatā vā asaṅkhatā vā, virāgo tesaṃ "
"aggamakkhāyati, yadidaṃ madanimmadano pipāsavinayo ālayasamugghāto "
"vaṭṭupacchedo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Fading away is said to be the best of all things whether conditioned or "
"unconditioned. That is, the quelling of vanity, the removing of thirst, the "
"abolishing of clinging, the breaking of the round, the ending of craving, "
"fading away, cessation, extinguishment."

msgctxt "an4.34:3.2"
msgid "Ye, bhikkhave, virāge dhamme pasannā, agge te pasannā."
msgstr ""
"Those who have confidence in the teaching of fading away have confidence in "
"the best."

msgctxt "an4.34:3.3"
msgid "Agge kho pana pasannānaṃ aggo vipāko hoti."
msgstr "Having confidence in the best, the result is the best."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.35"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.34:4.1"
msgid ""
"Yāvatā, bhikkhave, saṅghā vā gaṇā vā, tathāgatasāvakasaṅgho tesaṃ "
"aggamakkhāyati, yadidaṃ cattāri purisayugāni aṭṭha purisapuggalā esa "
"bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho āhuneyyo pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo "
"anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa."
msgstr ""
"The Saṅgha of the Realized One’s disciples is said to be the best of all "
"communities and groups. It consists of the four pairs, the eight "
"individuals. This Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is worthy of offerings "
"dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’s "
"offering, and worthy of veneration with joined palms. It is a supreme field "
"of merit for the world."

msgctxt "an4.34:4.2"
msgid "Ye, bhikkhave, saṅghe pasannā, agge te pasannā."
msgstr "Those who have confidence in the Saṅgha have confidence in the best."

msgctxt "an4.34:4.3"
msgid "Agge kho pana pasannānaṃ aggo vipāko hoti."
msgstr "Having confidence in the best, the result is the best."

msgctxt "an4.34:4.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro aggappasādāti."
msgstr "These are the four best kinds of confidence."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.34:5.1"
msgid "Aggato ve pasannānaṃ,"
msgstr "Those whose confidence comes from the best,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:5.2"
msgid "aggaṃ dhammaṃ vijānataṃ;"
msgstr "understand the principle of the best."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:5.3"
msgid "Agge buddhe pasannānaṃ,"
msgstr "Those confident in the best Buddha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:5.4"
msgid "dakkhiṇeyye anuttare."
msgstr "supremely worthy of a teacher’s offering;"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an4.34:6.1"
msgid "Agge dhamme pasannānaṃ,"
msgstr "those confident in the best teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:6.2"
msgid "virāgūpasame sukhe;"
msgstr "the bliss of fading away and stilling;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:6.3"
msgid "Agge saṅghe pasannānaṃ,"
msgstr "those confident in the best Saṅgha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:6.4"
msgid "puññakkhette anuttare."
msgstr "supreme field of merit:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an4.34:7.1"
msgid "Aggasmiṃ dānaṃ dadataṃ,"
msgstr "when they give gifts to the best,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:7.2"
msgid "aggaṃ puññaṃ pavaḍḍhati;"
msgstr "the best merit grows;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:7.3"
msgid "Aggaṃ āyu ca vaṇṇo ca,"
msgstr "the best lifespan, beauty,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:7.4"
msgid "yaso kitti sukhaṃ balaṃ."
msgstr "fame, reputation, happiness, and strength."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an4.34:8.1"
msgid "Aggassa dātā medhāvī,"
msgstr "An intelligent person gives to the best,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:8.2"
msgid "aggadhammasamāhito;"
msgstr "settled on the best teaching."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:8.3"
msgid "Devabhūto manusso vā,"
msgstr "When they become a god or human,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:8.4"
msgid "aggappatto pamodatī”ti."
msgstr "they rejoice at reaching the best.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.34:8.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
